wiki.content:
"Supremacy" is a song by English alternative rock band Muse, opening track and fourth single for their sixth studio album, The 2nd Law. The song was written by Matthew Bellamy.
 According to frontman Matthew Bellamy, "Supremacy" sees the band going to "absurd levels", while according to the French magazine Jeuxactu the song has elements of "Kashmir" from Led Zeppelin in its guitar riff and orchestration.
 The music video was released on February 2, 2013 through the NME website. It features people with black metal corpse paint doing extreme sports like BMX and surfing while Muse plays the song.
 The song was mixed as part of the entrance song for professional wrestler Manik beginning in 2013 on the Total Nonstop Action Wrestling promotion.
